$ Colors
@ color

{ Munsell colour system

  Apparently, the human eye can distinguish approx 100 colors in the spectrum of a rainbow.

  That's why the *Munsell colour system* distinguishes 100 hues.

}
{ RGB / HSV etc. conversion

  → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus[C/C++]: → https://github.com/aleksandaratanasov/RGBConverter, apparently obsolted by → https://github.com/FastLED/FastLED.

  → development/languages/JavaScript: → https://stackoverflow.com/questions/17242144/javascript-convert-hsb-hsv-color-to-rgb-accurately

}
{ Color names in CSS #css-color-names

  → development/web/CSS allows to specify colors with *color names*.

  → https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/X11_color_names[X11 color names] were the basis for → https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Web_colors[web colors].

  → https://www.w3.org/TR/css-color-3/#svg-color[This (SVG) list] provides X11 colors (with the addition of gray/grey variants from SVG 1.0) that are supported by popular
  → development/web/browser[browsers] along with their hexadecimal and decimal representation (compare this list with → https://www.w3.org/TR/2011/REC-SVG11-20110816/types.html#ColorKeywords[Recognized color keyword names])

}
